
@startuml

' Set skin to classic for clarity
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor Black
}

class Contract {
    +String id
    +Date startDate
    +Date endDate
    +String deliveryConditions
    +String legalTerms
}

class Acquisition {
    +String acquisitionId
    +int quantity
    +Date deliveryDate
    +double negotiatedPrice
    +String customizations
}

class Aircraft {
    +String model
    +int capacity
    +String configuration
}

class AirlineCompany {
    +String name
    +String country
    +String parentCompany (optional)
    +List<AirlineCompany> subsidiaries
}

class Salesperson {
    +String employeeId
    +String name
    +String department
}

' Relationships
Contract "1" -- "0..*" Acquisition : contains
Contract "1" -- "1" Salesperson : managed by
Contract "1" -- "1" AirlineCompany : signed with

Acquisition "1" -- "1" Aircraft : includes
Acquisition "1" -- "1" AirlineCompany : delivered to

AirlineCompany "1" -- "0..*" AirlineCompany : has subsidiary > (parent-child)

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Contract`**: Represents the overarching agreement between Boeing and an airline company.
  - May contain multiple `Acquisition`s.
  - Managed by one `Salesperson`.

- **`Acquisition`**: Each acquisition is for one or more aircrafts, with specific terms like price, delivery date, etc.
  - Linked to a single `Aircraft` model and assigned to an `AirlineCompany`.

- **`Aircraft`**: Describes the type/model of the aircraft being acquired.

- **`AirlineCompany`**: Tracks airlines and their hierarchical relationships (e.g., parent/child companies).
  - One airline can have many subsidiaries.

- **`Salesperson`**: A Boeing employee who manages contracts.
  - One salesperson can manage multiple contracts over time.

